race.comment: WOLF JUNIOR (7) returns today after placing at his last run over 1600m at Hobart on August 31. He will be a lot stronger now, and with a trial under his belt, he is the one to beat for ours. COLONEL BOGEY (12) is a promising type who hasn't raced since finishing fourth over 1200m at Hobart four months ago. He looked sharp after a recent trial win, and fresh up, he should go close to taking this out. FIERCE 'N FABULOUS (13) finished fourth on debut as a juvenile at Sale, and it won't take her long to make her mark in this State. Watch the market moves. GEEGEES MERCEDES (10) was not far away from the winner fresh up when third at Hobart 17 days ago. She has the pole position here, and can figure in the top 3 again.
